CVE-2026-33871  # HIGH | netty-codec-http2: DoS via HTTP/2 CONTINUATION — embedded in KC 26.6.1 JARs; fix requires KC to ship netty 4.1.132 | Added: 2026-05-08 | Review: 2026-05-22
CVE-2026-42577  # HIGH | netty-transport-native-epoll: DoS via RST on half-closed TCP — embedded in KC 26.6.1 JARs; fix requires KC to ship netty 4.2.13 | Added: 2026-05-08 | Review: 2026-05-22
CVE-2026-42579  # HIGH | netty-codec-dns: input validation bypass — embedded in KC 26.6.1 JARs; fix requires KC to ship netty 4.1.133 | Added: 2026-05-08 | Review: 2026-05-22
CVE-2026-42583  # HIGH | netty-codec: Lz4FrameDecoder resource exhaustion — embedded in KC 26.6.1 JARs; fix requires KC to ship netty 4.1.133 | Added: 2026-05-08 | Review: 2026-05-22
CVE-2026-42584  # HIGH | netty-codec-http: HttpClientCodec desync — embedded in KC 26.6.1 JARs; fix requires KC to ship netty 4.1.133 | Added: 2026-05-08 | Review: 2026-05-22
CVE-2026-42587  # HIGH | netty-codec-http/http2: decompression bypass — embedded in KC 26.6.1 JARs; fix requires KC to ship netty 4.1.133 | Added: 2026-05-08 | Review: 2026-05-22

